record_data.record_plain_text:
? EXHIBIT A
SERVICES SCOPE OF WORK
. Services are limited to work necessary to complete the Upgrade, including pre-construction, installation, implementation, and testing of the Upgrade, but do not extend to other tasks Affected Party may wish to complete during the Fall 2024 Planned Outage. Pursuant to the foregoing, Services include but are not limited to the following:
1. Work order planning – package development a. Provide supervision for NEE work orders b. Staff planning activities for electrical, mechanical, and I&C components as well as any activities necessary to support work c. Staff planning activities for all testing associated work 2. Craft services for implementation and Testing a. Carpentry, General labor, Ironworking, Electrical, Pipefitting, Operating engineering, Teamsters 3. Training Qualifications & Mock-up a. Provide training for Main Generator Breaker and Crane Certification. b. Provide OPS Support Clearances and Testing Support c. Provide mock-up training for field work and Testing activities 4. Install new Main Generator Breaker Crane a. MASS Crane b. Westinghouse/BHI Support for crane 5. Install ISO Phase Bus Duct Cooler a. Westinghouse / BHI Installation of IPBD Cooling Skid b. RMS/Hitachi ISO Phase Bus Duct Cleaning/Inspection Support 6. RMS/Hitachi build and installation of Main Generator Breaker a. Westinghouse/BHI Main Generator Breaker Support b. Westinghouse scaffold build for Bus Duct inspections c. RMS additional welders for gained margin 7. WCS Framatome DCS Translator and HMI for Simulator 8. Phoenix splicing a. Testing support: Metrology, ME, I&C, and MM 9. Testing a. Development of all test procedures and instructions b. Performance of all functional testing, post maintenance testing and site acceptance testing c. Support of all testing activities 10. Construction management 11. Quality control and non-destructive examinations 12. Project management 13. Scheduling and cost estimation, and tracking 14. Direct management and station overhead support which includes, but is not limited to: a. Enhanced security support including barrier removal and re-installation b. Facilities cleaning and repair support c. Fitness for duty testing d. IT services associated with the upgrade e. Maintenance support for material and equipment movement, and emergent needs f. Management observations, project assessments, and challenges g. Outage control center support during critical path, and outage scheduler h. Outage trailer rental, set-up, temporary power, and communications i. Portable restroom rental and cleaning j. Quality assurance support k. Site access and in-processing l. Support for tagging and systems alignment m. Support from safety and on-site medical teams n. Tool Crib attendant support o. Trash and waste disposal services
